<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">History</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="position-relative p-0">
                    <img class="img-fluid w-100 object-fit-cover" src="/img/banners/history.png" />
                    <div class="position-absolute bottom-0 end-0 p-3 w-50">
                        <div class="bg-black p-3 bg-opacity-75 rounded shadow">
                            <span class="lora-medium fst-italic text-light">
                                When every kingdom has buried enough sons, even rivals discover the value of peace.
                            </span>
                            <span></span>
                            <div class="lora-semibold text-light text-end mt-2">
                                King Nicholas II, The Royal Histories
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            Aeld is an ancient world shaped by the rise and fall of civilizations over eons.
                            Though monsters, magic, and forgotten ruins exist, they are exceptions rather than the rule.
                            Most people spend their lives farming fertile valleys, working crowded cities, serving noble
                            houses, or traveling the trade roads that connect the world's great powers.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            For adventurers, Aeld is more than a backdrop. It is where reputations are
                            earned, alliances are forged, and fortunes are spent. Between adventures, its cities offer
                            opportunities to train, conduct research, pursue personal ambitions, and prepare for the
                            next journey.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Commonwealth</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Commonwealth encompasses the settled heart of Aeld, where kingdoms, city-states, and
                            free lands stand connected by ancient roads, thriving trade, and centuries of shared
                            history. The Commonwealth is a loose alliance of sovereign realms bound by the Royal
                            Accords, a living document and binding covenant governing diplomacy, trade, and mutual
                            obligations between its members.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Under the provisions of the Accords, merchants carry goods across the continent, pilgrims
                            journey between sacred sites, scholars exchange knowledge, and envoys work tirelessly to
                            preserve an often fragile peace. For most people, the Commonwealth is more of a concept than
                            a governing force. It keeps borders open, commerce moving, and diplomacy possible, but
                            beyond its broad principles, it is often overshadowed by local traditions, political
                            rivalries, and practical necessity.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">Royal Enclave</h6>
                        <p>
                            At the heart of the Commonwealth, towering walls protect generations of history, wealth, and
                            knowledge in the Royal Enclave. Home to foundational institutions like the Royal Court, the
                            High Council, and the Grand Archives, it serves as the political, cultural, and ceremonial
                            epicenter of the known world.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">Principalities</h6>
                        <p>
                            A Principality is a broad territorial kingdom ruled from a prominent regional capital. Its
                            authority encompasses numerous towns and villages, productive farmland, natural resources,
                            and established trade routes, making it a lasting center of political, economic, and
                            military power.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">Noble Estates</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Noble Estates are self-governing city-states ruled by legendary noble houses, each with
                            its own laws, customs, and ambitions. Though united under the Commonwealth's charter, they
                            remain fiercely independent, competing through diplomacy, trade, and political influence
                            rather than outright conquest.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">The Heartlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Heartlands are an informal network of farming communities, mining towns, and local
                            markets that keep the realm supplied. Small villages and market towns are woven together by
                            well-traveled roads, rivers, and trade routes, ensuring food, timber, ore, and stone reach
                            every corner of the Commonwealth.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>